
Instructions for generating a PKI for Medulla:
1. Edit create-pki.sh and define the following settings:
      PASSPHRASE          : The passphrase to be used for the private keys
      CRL_SERVER_ADDRESS  : The address of the server that will host the revocation list (http://@@CRL_SERVER_ADDRESS@@/crl.pem)
   Also change PKI_ORGANIZATION if needs be
2. Run the script named create-pki.sh



Instructions for revocating a certificate:
1. Run the following command:
      openssl ca -config /var/lib/medulla/pki/conf/medulla.cnf \
        -revoke /var/lib/medulla/pki/<certificate.pem>
   You will be asked to provide the passphrase protecting the CA key (cakey.pem)
2. Generate the revocation list:
      openssl ca -config /var/lib/medulla/pki/conf/medulla.cnf \
        -name CA_Intermediate -gencrl -out /var/lib/medulla/pki/crl.pem
3. Check that the list is correct:
      openssl crl -in /var/lib/medulla/pki/crl.pem -noout -text
4. Copy the file /var/lib/medulla/pki/crl.pem to the server defined in CRL_SERVER_ADDRESS

### Please note that the crl has a validity period of 30 days. ###
### The file needs to be regenerated every 30 days (steps 2-4) ###



Instructions for generating a new certificate:
1. Generate the key and sign request:
      openssl req -config /var/lib/medulla/pki/conf/medulla.cnf \
        -subj "/countryName=FR/organizationName=SIVEO/commonName=<FQDN_OF_SERVER>" \
        -batch -extensions server_cert -new \
        -keyout /var/lib/medulla/pki/private/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.key.pem \
        -out /var/lib/medulla/pki/req/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.req.pem
2. Sign the certificate with the PKI:
      openssl ca -config /var/lib/medulla/pki/conf/medulla.cnf \
        -name CA_Intermediate -batch -extensions server_cert \
        -keyfile /var/lib/medulla/pki/private/cakey.pem \
        -out /var/lib/medulla/pki/newcerts/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.cert.pem \
        -infiles /var/lib/medulla/pki/req/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.req.pem
   You will be asked to provide the passphrase protecting the CA key (cakey.pem)
3. Generate the final certificate:
      openssl rsa -in /var/lib/medulla/pki/private/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.key.pem \
        -out /var/lib/medulla/pki/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.pem
      cat /var/lib/medulla/pki/newcerts/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.cert.pem \
        >> /var/lib/medulla/pki/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.pem
4. Set the proper permissions on the generated files:
      chmod 400 /var/lib/medulla/pki/private/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.key.pem
      chmod 444 /var/lib/medulla/pki/newcerts/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.cert.pem
      chmod 444 /var/lib/medulla/pki/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.pem
5. Do some cleanup:
      rm /var/lib/medulla/pki/req/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.req.pem

The certificate to be used is /var/lib/medulla/pki/<FQDN_OF_SERVER>.pem
The ca certificate to be used is /var/lib/medulla/pki/ca-chain.cert.pem
